'Germanium dioxide', also called 'germanium oxide' and 'germania', is an
inorganic compound, an oxide of germanium. Its chemical formula is
GeO 2. Other names include '{{not a typo|germanic}} acid', 'G-15', and
'ACC10380'. It forms as a passivation layer on pure germanium in contact with
atmospheric oxygen.
